{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Trees epitomize stasis."},{"time":4000,"text":"Trees are rooted in the ground in one place"},{"time":6000,"text":"for many human generations,"},{"time":9000,"text":"but if we shift our perspective"},{"time":11000,"text":"from the trunk to the twigs,"},{"time":13000,"text":"trees become very dynamic entities,"},{"time":15000,"text":"moving and growing."},{"time":17000,"text":"And I decided to explore this movement"},{"time":19000,"text":"by turning trees into artists."},{"time":21000,"text":"I simply tied the end of a paintbrush onto a twig."},{"time":24000,"text":"I waited for the wind to come up and held up a canvas,"},{"time":27000,"text":"and that produced art."},{"time":29000,"text":"The piece of art you see on your left"},{"time":31000,"text":"is painted by a western red cedar"},{"time":33000,"text":"and that on your right by a Douglas fir,"},{"time":35000,"text":"and what I learned was that different species"},{"time":37000,"text":"have different signatures, like a Picasso versus a Monet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"But I was also interested in the movement of trees"},{"time":42000,"text":"and how this art might let me capture that and quantify it,"},{"time":46000,"text":"so to measure the distance that a single vine maple tree --"},{"time":49000,"text":"which produced this painting -- moved in a single year,"},{"time":52000,"text":"I simply measured and summed"},{"time":54000,"text":"each of those lines."},{"time":56000,"text":"I multiplied them by the number of twigs per branch"},{"time":59000,"text":"and the number of branches per tree"},{"time":61000,"text":"and then divided that by the number of minutes per year."},{"time":64000,"text":"And so I was able to calculate"},{"time":66000,"text":"how far a single tree moved in a single year."},{"time":69000,"text":"You might have a guess."},{"time":71000,"text":"The answer is actually 186,540 miles,"},{"time":74000,"text":"or seven times around the globe."},{"time":77000,"text":"And so simply by shifting our perspective from a single trunk"},{"time":80000,"text":"to the many dynamic twigs,"},{"time":82000,"text":"we are able to see that trees are not simply static entities,"},{"time":85000,"text":"but rather extremely dynamic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"And I began to think about ways that"},{"time":90000,"text":"we might consider this lesson of trees,"},{"time":92000,"text":"to consider other entities that are also static and stuck,"},{"time":95000,"text":"but which cry for change and dynamicism,"},{"time":98000,"text":"and one of those entities is our prisons."},{"time":101000,"text":"Prisons, of course, are where people who break our laws"},{"time":103000,"text":"are stuck, confined behind bars."},{"time":106000,"text":"And our prison system itself is stuck."},{"time":109000,"text":"The United States has over 2.3 million"},{"time":111000,"text":"incarcerated men and women."},{"time":113000,"text":"That number is rising."},{"time":115000,"text":"Of the 100 incarcerated people that are released,"},{"time":118000,"text":"60 will return to prison."},{"time":120000,"text":"Funds for education, for training"},{"time":122000,"text":"and for rehabilitation are declining,"},{"time":124000,"text":"so this despairing cycle of incarceration continues."},{"time":128000,"text":"I decided to ask whether the lesson"},{"time":130000,"text":"I had learned from trees as artists"},{"time":132000,"text":"could be applied to a static institution"},{"time":134000,"text":"such as our prisons,"},{"time":136000,"text":"and I think the answer is yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"In the year 2007,"},{"time":140000,"text":"I started a partnership"},{"time":142000,"text":"with the Washington State Department of Corrections."},{"time":145000,"text":"Working with four prisons, we began bringing science and scientists,"},{"time":148000,"text":"sustainability and conservation projects"},{"time":151000,"text":"to four state prisons."},{"time":153000,"text":"We give science lectures,"},{"time":155000,"text":"and the men here are choosing to come to our science lectures"},{"time":157000,"text":"instead of watching television or weightlifting."},{"time":161000,"text":"That, I think, is movement."},{"time":163000,"text":"We partnered with the Nature Conservancy"},{"time":165000,"text":"for inmates at Stafford Creek Correctional Center"},{"time":168000,"text":"to grow endangered prairie plants"},{"time":170000,"text":"for restoration of relic prairie areas in Washington state."},{"time":173000,"text":"That, I think, is movement."},{"time":175000,"text":"We worked with the Washington State Department of Fish and Wildlife"},{"time":178000,"text":"to grow endangered frogs -- the Oregon spotted frog --"},{"time":180000,"text":"for later release into protected wetlands."},{"time":183000,"text":"That, I think, is movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"And just recently, we've begun to work with"},{"time":188000,"text":"those men who are segregated"},{"time":190000,"text":"in what we call Supermax facilities."},{"time":192000,"text":"They've incurred violent infractions"},{"time":194000,"text":"by becoming violent with guards"},{"time":196000,"text":"and with other prisoners."},{"time":198000,"text":"They're kept in bare cells like this"},{"time":200000,"text":"for 23 hours a day."},{"time":202000,"text":"When they have meetings with their review boards or mental health professionals,"},{"time":205000,"text":"they're placed in immobile booths like this."},{"time":208000,"text":"For one hour a day"},{"time":210000,"text":"they're brought to these bleak and bland exercise yards."},{"time":213000,"text":"Although we can't bring trees and prairie plants"},{"time":215000,"text":"and frogs into these environments,"},{"time":217000,"text":"we are bringing images of nature"},{"time":219000,"text":"into these exercise yards,"},{"time":221000,"text":"putting them on the walls, so at least they get contact"},{"time":223000,"text":"with visual images of nature."},{"time":226000,"text":"This is Mr. Lopez, who has been in solitary confinement for 18 months,"},{"time":229000,"text":"and he's providing input on the types of images"},{"time":232000,"text":"that he believes would make him and his fellow inmates"},{"time":234000,"text":"more serene, more calm,"},{"time":237000,"text":"less apt to violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240000,"text":"And so what we see, I think,"},{"time":242000,"text":"is that small, collective movements of change"},{"time":245000,"text":"can perhaps move"},{"time":247000,"text":"an entity such as our own prison system"},{"time":250000,"text":"in a direction of hope."},{"time":252000,"text":"We know that trees are static entities"},{"time":255000,"text":"when we look at their trunks."},{"time":257000,"text":"But if trees can create art,"},{"time":259000,"text":"if they can encircle the globe seven times in one year,"},{"time":262000,"text":"if prisoners can grow plants and raise frogs,"},{"time":265000,"text":"then perhaps there are other static entities"},{"time":268000,"text":"that we hold inside ourselves,"},{"time":271000,"text":"like grief, like addictions,"},{"time":273000,"text":"like racism,"},{"time":275000,"text":"that can also change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}